Foot-and-mouth disease virus, Zambia
------------------------------------
General information
Report type: Immediate notification
Started: [16 Jun 2021]
Confirmed: [1 Aug 2021]
Reported: 27 Aug 2021
Reason for notification: Recurrence
Last occurrence: 20 Aug 2019
Causal agent: Foot-and-mouth disease virus
Subtype: Not typed
Nature of diagnosis: Clinical
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

Outbreak location 1: Sindamisale, Chadiza, Eastern
Date of start of the outbreak: 29 Mar 2021
Epidemiological unit: Village
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered or killed for commercial use / Vaccinated
Cattle / 120 / 55 / 0 / 0 / 0 / -

Outbreak location 2: Kanyunya veterinary camp, Lundazi, Eastern
Date of start of the outbreak: 31 Mar 2021
Epidemiological unit: Village
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered or killed for commercial use / Vaccinated
Cattle / 67 / 11 / 0 / 0 / 0 / -

Outbreak location 3: Mambolomka veterinary camp, Shangombo, Western
Date of start of the outbreak: 31 Jul 2021
Epidemiological unit: Village
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered or killed for commercial use / Vaccinated
Cattle / 2500 / 9 / 0 / 0 / 0 / -

Outbreak location 4: Senanga central veterinary camp, Senanga, Western
Date of start of the outbreak: 16 Jun 2021
Epidemiological unit: Village
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered or killed for commercial use / Vaccinated
Cattle / 70 / 7 / 0 / 0 / 0 / -

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Contact with infected animal(s) at grazing/watering points; illegal movement of animals
Epidemiological comments: Cattle affected were of all ages under free-range traditional management. The disease was spread through illegal cattle movements.

Control measures at event level
Domestic control measures applied: Movement control inside the country, quarantine, screening, surveillance outside containment and/or the protection zone, surveillance within containment and/or the protection zone, traceability

Diagnostic test results: [Not available]

[The location of the outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

