[Foot-and-mouth disease (FMD) is endemic in Zambia. The following information is available from the WRLFMD-Pirbright Institute web site at http://www.wrlfmd.org/southern-africa/zambia#panel-6551.

FMDV serotype / Years (not comprehensive)
-----------------------------------------
Untyped / 1932-1933
O / 1976, 1982, 2000, 2010, 2018-2020
A / 1990, 2015, 2018
SAT 1 / Livestock: 1953-1955, 1973-1974, 1979-1981, 1987-1988, 2000, 2004-2005, 2008-2009, 2012; Buffalo: 1993, 1996
SAT 2 / Livestock: 1948, 1950, 1956-1958, 1960, 1964-1965, 1969, 1975, 1981-1982, 2007-2009, 2012, 2015, 2019; Buffalo: 1993, 1996
SAT 3 / Livestock: 2015, 2017; Buffalo: 1974, 1993, 1996

Note: All 3 SAT serotypes are probably endemic in the African buffalo (_Syncerus caffer_) population.

EUFMD's Quarterly FMD Situation Report, covering April-June 2021 (see ref 1), mentioned for Zambia that: "On 8 June 2021, a batch of 97 samples was received. The results of serotyping and genotyping are pending."

Reference
---------
1. FAO/EUFMD. Foot-and-mouth disease, quarterly report. April-June 2021. Rome: FAO; http://www.fao.org/3/cb5998en/cb5998en.pdf
- Mod.CRD

